               <msContents>
                  <summary>
                     This unsigned and undated copy of the <title>Mas̲navī-i Ma‘navī</title> (Spiritual Couplets) by <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/98930150" key="person_98930150">Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī
                        (1207–1273)</persName> bears delicately illuminated headers on the prefaces and six books. The seals and notations suggest that a Mughal-era scribe probably completed it in the <date cert="medium" calendar="#Gregorian" from="1700" to="1800">17th century</date>. 
                  </summary>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_847-item1">
                     <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/98930150" key="person_98930150">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">جلال الدین رومی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20506" change="#ids-cleanup">Mas̲navī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20506" change="#ids-cleanup">مثنوی</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla">
                        <locus type="page" from="2" to="2"> صفحه‌ی ۲ (Page 2):</locus>
                        برگ ۱پ بشنو از نی چون حکایت میکند * و ز جدأیها شکایت میکند
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus type="page" from="772" to="772"> صفحه‌ی ۷۷۲ (Page 772):</locus>
                        در دل من آن سخن زان میمنه‌ست *
                        
                        زانک از دل جانب دل روزنه‌ست
                     </explicit>
                     <colophon>No colophon.</colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_847-item1-item1">
                        <locus type="page" from="2" to="2">2</locus>
